f I redefine the class `Q8_0Block` in HolyC, especially since both it and `Q4_0Block` may be included together. To avoid compilation errors, I should probably define the class locally without redefining it in each file.\n\nI’ll want to examine existing definitions to see if it’s safe to compile them separately. Also, I need to set up some tests with a pure Python model using functions imported from `test_q8_0_dot`. Adding a helper for the `Q8_0MatMul` function would be beneficial, but maybe creating a standalone test file is the best route.\n**Setting up and implementing updates**\n\nFirst, I need to create a new directory and file for matrix multiplication. I’ll check for any AGENTS in the parent directory since that could affect my implementation. I'll include inline comments as I go. After that, I’ll run a validation command with Python to ensure everything is working correctly.\n\nI also need to update the MASTER_TASKS: noting that IQ-099 is completed and checking the queue size to keep it at 15 or more unchecked tasks. I’ll add a line in the progress ledger below the header, using the latest loop ID. Lastly, I'll prepare to insert changes in the central database and utilize the patch tool as instructed."}}
